in/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:91:        // Ensure the tests build.gradle has an agent block; if not, create user-code-filter.json and add the agent block.\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/DockerTask.java:54:                    + new URI(\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#providing-the-tests-that-use-docker\\\"));\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/DockerTask.java:66:                        + new URI(\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#providing-the-tests-that-use-docker\\\"));\\n./docs/architecture.md:25:| `metadata/` | The shipped product: per-artifact `index.json` and per-version `reachability-metadata.json`, plus the master library list and schemas. | §METADATA-suite |\\n./docs/metadata.md:18:  `allowed-packages`, the source/test/documentation/repository URLs, and optional\\n./docs/metadata.md:22:- `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\\n./docs/metadata.md:25:  single-file format of the vendored `reachability-metadata` schema. The legacy\\n./docs/metadata.md:33:  (`reachability-metadata`, `metadata-library-index`,\\n./docs/metadata.md:45:gap. The entry carries no `tested-versions` or `allowed-packages`, and\\n./docs/metadata.md:50:- **Conditional on `typeReached`, and nothing else.** Every reachability-metadata\\n./docs/metadata.md:55:  inside the artifact's `allowed-packages`, and no entry may target a test-only\\n./docs/metadata.md:60:  `reachability-metadata` and `metadata-library-index` schemas follow semver\\n./docs/metadata.md:63:  non-plugin formats), while a **major bump (e.g. `reachability-metadata` 1.2.0 →\\n./docs/metadata.md:80:`metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json` and into the\\n./docs/metadata.md:82:`tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:57:    private static final String USER_CODE_FILTER_FILE = \\\"user-code-filter.json\\\";\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:160:     * Creates a user-code-filter.json file including the given library packages plus any\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:374:        List<Path> inputDirectories = Files.isRegularFile(durableMetadataDirectory.resolve(\\\"reachability-metadata.json\\\"))\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:389:        Path mergedMetadataFile = mergedMetadataDirectory.resolve(\\\"reachability-metadata.json\\\");\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:394:        Files.copy(mergedMetadataFile, durableMetadataDirectory.resolve(\\\"reachability-metadata.json\\\"), StandardCopyOption.REPLACE_EXISTING);\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:435:                entry.put(\\\"allowed-packages\\\", new ArrayList<>(allowedPackages));\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:478:        Object currentPackages = entry.get(\\\"allowed-packages\\\");\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:680:                latestAllowedPackages, // allowed-packages\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:31:Two properties make this achievable: the reachability-metadata schema is itself additive (every entry is gated on `typeReached`), and `native-image` defaults to runtime initialization when no build-time directives are supplied. The hard constraints below preserve that additivity — they are not editorial scope choices but direct consequences of the invariant.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:57:- Validation that every metadata entry uses `typeReached` and stays inside `allowed-packages`.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:137:    participant Repo as graalvm-reachability-metadata\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:159:**1. Distribution artifact.** The `package` Gradle task produces `graalvm-reachability-metadata-<repo-version>.zip`, which the scheduled release workflow attaches as a GitHub Release asset on a `<repo-version>` tag every two weeks. The ZIP is a verbatim copy of the repository's `metadata/` directory — there is no separate top-level manifest. Its contents at the ZIP root are exactly:\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:166:    reachability-metadata-schema-vX.Y.Z.json\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:169:    reachability-metadata.json                           # the only file native-image loads (element 3)\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:172:Plugin-relevant content is `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` and the per-version `reachability-metadata.json` files; the plugin discovers libraries by directory walk. `library-and-framework-list.json` and `schemas/` are present for downstream tooling (the libraries-and-frameworks page and offline validators) and are not consumed by native-build-tools at native-image time.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:174:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\\\"<group>:<artifact>\\\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:180:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry's `condition` carries exactly one key, `typeReached`, so the plugin can rely on conditional registration; `typeReached` is the schema's only condition form. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:210:All four elements are versioned through the schema `$id` URLs and the GitHub Release tag. Newer plugins keep reading older repository releases, and older plugins keep reading newer **minor and patch** schema versions, which only add optional fields or non-plugin formats. A **major** schema bump (e.g. `reachability-metadata` 1.2.0 → 2.0.0, or `metadata-library-index` 2.x → 3.0.0) represents a change native-build-tools must adopt and is released together with a coordinated plugin update — it is not something older plugins absorb. Schema fidelity (§6) and the bi-weekly release cadence (§4.4) keep this contract live.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:218:- **Allowed-package conditions.** Every metadata entry's `typeReached` condition must reference a class inside the artifact's `allowed-packages`.\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:222:- **Dependency and test-only split.** Metadata can declare dependencies on other artifacts via `requires`. Metadata needed only by the tests — entries whose type or `typeReached` names a test package, or whose resource is a test resource — must not ship to consumers; `splitTestOnlyMetadata` moves them out of the library's `reachability-metadata.json` into the test project's `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`, keeping the shipped metadata free of test-only types (§METADATA-suite).\\n./docs/functional-spec.md:361:canonical `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata` repository. Each run discovers\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:3:description: Create a GitHub issue and pull request in oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata, link the PR to the issue, and request reviews from the standard reviewer set except the PR author.\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:10:`oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata` and request the standard reviewer set\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:37:     -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\\\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:55:     -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\\\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:69:     -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\\\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:75:   gh pr view PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json number,url,reviewRequests,closingIssuesReferences\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:76:   gh issue view ISSUE_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json number,url,state\\n./docs/tck.md:42:| `checkMetadataFiles` | Every entry uses `condition.typeReached`, stays inside `allowed-packages`, and references no test-only types (§METADATA-suite, §FS-repository-functional-spec.5.1). |\\n./docs/tck.md:82:| `generateMetadata` | Generate metadata for a coordinate (optionally deriving `user-code-filter.json` from the resolved JAR). |\\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:14:        userCodeFilterPath = \\\"user-code-filter.json\\\"\\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:32:A sample filter file (user-code-filter.json) for a library whose classes are all contained in `com.acme`:\\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:49:        userCodeFilterPath = \\\"user-code-filter.json\\\"\\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:73:native-image-configure generate-conditional --user-code-filter=user-code-filter.json --class-name-filter=extra-code-filter.json --input-dir=<agent-output-dir> --input-dir=<agent-output-dir-2>... --output-dir=final-metadata/\\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:7:Fetches open issues from the graalvm-reachability-metadata project board,\\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:18:      [--strategy-name <name>] [--reachability-metadata-path 